metadata.name: Against All Odds.
metadata.description:
When is a time you have accomplished something beyond your imagination? Or pushed yourself a little further than your preconceived belief?

You are capable against all odds.

This image came on a night of -35C.  As the time passed midnight, everyone drove home as the aurora was faint in appearance.  I had it in my gut to stay, even if it meant breaks in the car to warm up. I just had a feeling she was trying to come out this night.  

Seemingly against all odds, we got an awe-inspiring show at 02:00am.

This is NOT a composite. My partner and I took our tent and weighed in down in the middle of a frozen lake and photographed it while trying not to think of the cold.  The aurora is particularly difficult down here and it truly isnâ€™t all that common to see. A balance of science and magic reveal this  sought after phenomenon.
